# Trivy Ignore File
# Format: CVE-ID | Package | Justification
# Updated: 2026-04-06
# Review quarterly or when new CVEs are discovered

# ============================================================================
# PYTHON PACKAGES
# ============================================================================

# urllib3 - Required for HTTP requests, no alternative available
# Fixed in next release but upgrading breaks compatibility with older Python
CVE-2024-xxxxx|urllib3|Required dependency, upgrading breaks older Python versions

# requests - Running behind authenticated proxy provides mitigation
# Alternative: No drop-in replacement without significant refactoring
CVE-2024-yyyyy|requests|Mitigated by authenticated proxy

# numpy - Security fix pending, low severity
# No immediate security impact in our use case
CVE-2023-XXXXX|numpy|Reviewing in next patch cycle

# ============================================================================
# NODE.JS PACKAGES
# ============================================================================

# axios - No known exploit path in our use case
# Request timeout configured, no user-controlled URLs
CVE-2024-ZZZZZ|axios|No exploit path, request validation in place

# ============================================================================
# OS PACKAGES
# ============================================================================

# libssl1.1 - Required by TensorFlow binary wheels
# No alternative available, GPU support depends on this
CVE-2023-zzzzz|libssl1.1|Required by TensorFlow, no alternative

# busybox - Container doesn't run as root
# No privilege escalation possible
CVE-2024-falsepositive|busybox|Container runs as non-root user

# openssl - System package, running latest version not possible without OS upgrade
# Mitigation in place via network policies
CVE-2023-YYYYY|openssl|System package, mitigation via network policies

# ============================================================================
# THIRD-PARTY CONTAINERS
# ============================================================================

# Keycloak base image - Aqua Security maintains official image
# Running latest version, CVE requires authenticated access
CVE-2024-KEYCLOAK-001|keycloak|Mitigated by network policies, Keycloak is internal only

# MLflow base image - Updated regularly
# No direct access to MLflow from external networks
CVE-2024-MLFLOW-001|mlflow|Internal service, network isolated

# ============================================================================
# REVIEW SCHEDULE
# ============================================================================
# This file should be reviewed:
# - Quarterly (Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct)
# - After any new CVE announcements for our dependencies
# - After upgrading any major dependency version
#
# When removing an ignore:
# 1. Verify the fix is available
# 2. Test the upgrade in staging
# 3. Update this file with removal date
# 4. Redeploy affected services

